Description: Limestone tomb relief: from the tomb of Nyibunesu. It is carved in good, but rather heavy, low relief with a representation of a palace-façade above which are the titles and name of Nyibunesu on the lintel. No colour remains.
Curator's comments: This slab was originally placed below tomb-relief (1898,0817.11). Published: B. Porter & R. Moss, 'Topographical Bibliography of Ancient Egyptian Hieroglyphic Texts, Reliefs and Paintings' V (Oxford: Clarendon Press), 110.
Bibliographic references: Scott-Moncrieff 1911 / Hieroglyphic texts from Egyptian stelae, etc., in the British Museum, Part 1. (pl.3)
James 1961 / Hieroglyphic texts from Egyptian stelae, etc. Part 1 (pl.12)
